    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Variable Geometry Turbocharger (VGT) -
        Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="s05.4">
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc id="s05.4.1" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="10">
            <title>Variable Geometry Turbocharger (VGT) Assembly and Components</title>
            <figure id="f3450005018" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figM15/M15104.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Turbo support</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M10 x 30 bolt (6)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbo support</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place a new turbo bracket gasket in engine valley.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place turbo support in engine valley.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If not immediately installing the turbocharger assembly, cover turbo oil drain hole with
                        <hotlnk document="eges3451_122.xml" xrefid="s05.t3">Turbo Oil Drain Plug ZTSE4785-2</hotlnk>
                        <xref refid="s05.t3"/>.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install six M10 x 30 bolts to secure turbo support to crankcase. Tighten bolts to
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_121.xml" xrefid="s05.t2">special torque</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s05.t2"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3450005019" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figM15/M15112.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Align turbocharger assembly exhaust outlet</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Align pin on turbocharger assembly exhaust outlet with hole in turbocharger assembly.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach turbocharger assembly exhaust outlet to turbocharger assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3450005020" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figM15/M15113.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Turbocharger assembly exhaust outlet</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust outlet V-clamp</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust outlet</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install turbocharger assembly exhaust outlet V-clamp and tighten to
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_121.xml" xrefid="s05.t2">special torque</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s05.t2"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_122.xml" xrefid="s05.t3">Turbo Oil Drain Plug ZTSE4785-2</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s05.t3"/>
                    from turbo support.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two new turbo oil drain tube O-rings and lubricate both O-rings with clean
                    engine oil.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3450005021" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figM15/M15106.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Turbo oil drain tube</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install turbo drain tube into turbo support.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove turbo oil drain tube cap (if installed) and lower turbocharger assembly on turbo
                    support and turbo oil drain tube.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3450005022" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figM15/M15105.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Turbocharger assembly mounting</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M10 x 35 bolt (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M10 stud bolt (2)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Coat threads of two M10 x 35 flange head bolts and two M10 stud bolts with anti-seize
                    compound and secure turbocharger assembly to turbo support.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten turbocharger assembly bolts and stud bolts to
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_121.xml" xrefid="s05.t2">special torque</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s05.t2"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_122.xml" xrefid="s05.t3">Turbo Oil Supply Block ZTSE4785-1</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s05.t3"/>
                    from oil filter base assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, lubricate turbocharger assembly bearings before installing the
                        turbocharger assembly.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate oil inlet hole of turbocharger assembly with clean engine oil and spin
                    compressor wheel several times to coat bearings with oil. Refill oil inlet hole up to oil supply
                    tube assembly mounting surface.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install and lubricate a new O-ring on turbo oil supply tube assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new O-ring on turbocharger assembly oil supply port.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3450005023" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figM15/M15100.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Turbo oil supply tube assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 20 bolt</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbo oil supply tube assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M6 x 20 bolt</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M8 stud bolt</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install turbo oil supply tube assembly in oil supply line port in oil filter base
                    assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install M6 x 20 turbo oil supply tube assembly to oil filter base assembly bolt. Tighten
                    bolt to
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_121.xml" xrefid="s05.t2">special torque</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s05.t2"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position oil supply tube flange over turbocharger assembly oil supply port and secure
                    with M8 x 20 bolt and M8 stud bolt.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Alternate tightening between bolt and stud bolt until correct torque is reached.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten turbo oil supply tube assembly to turbocharger bolt and stud bolt to
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_121.xml" xrefid="s05.t2">special torque</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s05.t2"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3450005024" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figM15/M15114.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>EGR top bracket washers</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Stud bolt (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">#10 washer (2)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place two #10 washers on turbocharger stud bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3450005025" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figM15/M15102.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Turbo heat shield</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbo heat shield</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M6 x 10 bolt (3)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install turbo heat shield on VGT.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install three M6&#160;x&#160;10 bolts and tighten to
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_121.xml" xrefid="s05.t2">special torque</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s05.t2"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3450005026" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figM15/M15103.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Turbo air inlet duct</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbo air inlet duct</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbo air inlet duct clamp</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install turbo air inlet duct on turbocharger assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Before tightening clamp, position the turbo air inlet duct according to the alignment marks
                        made during removal.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure turbo air inlet duct to turbocharger assembly by tightening clamp to
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_121.xml" xrefid="s05.t2">special torque</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s05.t2"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3450005027" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figM09/M09122.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>VGT actuator electrical connector</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect electrical connector to VGT actuator.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_103.xml" xrefid="s04.4.2.ref1">Exhaust Gas Recirculating (EGR) cooler
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s04.4.2.ref1"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
